# POSP Active / Inactive — Deal Activity Rule

**POSPs are never marked inactive manually in product flows.** The `Posp.active` column
in the database may be updated as a cache (`lastBusinessAt`, `autoInactive`), but the
**source of truth** is deal activity.

## Definition

| Status | Rule |
|--------|------|
| **Active** | At least one deal (`Deal.createdAt`) in the rolling last **30 days** |
| **Active (grace)** | Joined within the last 30 days and has **no deals yet** (onboarding window) |
| **Inactive** | No deal in the last 30 days **and** join date is older than 30 days |

Constants and helpers live in
[`server/src/common/business-rules/posp-activity.util.ts`](server/src/common/business-rules/posp-activity.util.ts).

## Where it applies

- POSP roster list + CSV export — `active` on API responses is **computed**
- Universal filter `active=true|false` — uses Prisma activity filters, not raw `Posp.active`
- Dashboard KPI `posps.active` — count of territorially scoped active POSPs
- Profile `posp.active` — computed for the viewed user
- On `DealCreatedEvent` — refresh `lastBusinessAt` + `active` on the linked POSP

## Do not

- Add UI for managers to toggle POSP active/inactive (synced roster only)
- Use Cognitensor upstream status as CRM active/inactive
- Change the threshold in one place only — update `POSP_INACTIVITY_THRESHOLD_DAYS` and this doc
